Title: White Space (Dark Passages, #1)
Author: Ilsa J. Bick
My Review:
This book is extremely confusing and very difficult to follow, especially for the first 150 pages of the book. It took me forever to get used to the writing style and get a grasp on what I was reading about. At the same time, I am very glad I persevered and pushed through to keep reading the book because this book is by far the most creative book I have ever read. Its probably not for everyone, and a lot of people will probably give up, but I must say, I really did enjoy it by the end of the book.
Give it a try, and maybe give yourself more time than you normally would to get a grasp on this book. I will definitely be reading the next one.

Title: Stolen
Author: Lucy Christopher
My Review:
This was a really good book. I loved everything from the writing and the characters. I must admit that I must have been living under a hole when I picked up this book. For whatever reason, I had not realized it was in the format of her writing a letter to her captor. When I got to the last chapter I had to go back and make sure I had read it right. After the shock wore off, I realized that I really like that Lucy had written the book that way and was thoroughly pleased.
I would recommend this to anyone looking for a comfortable read with a solid plot and interesting story.
